In Lean, for `f : U → V`, `Set.image f s` is `{y : V | ∃ x ∈ s, f x = y}`. 

Thus, `image g (image f s)` is `{x : U | ∃ y ∈ image f s, g y = x}` = `{x : U | ∃ (y : V), (∃ (z : U), z ∈ s ∧ f z = y) ∧ g y = x}`. 

But because `g ∘ f = id`, if we take `y = f z`, then `g y = g (f z) = z`. 

